title: Aw, Bucky, No.
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2wcSEj1

by Alexander_Slamilton

“ “Okay, please don’t be someone sent to kill me,” he pleads to the unopened door, there’s another knock. Clint opens the door, and there’s a guy who looks like Steve’s friend standing in the hall. What was his name? Not Lucky, that’s his dog. Something beginning with B. “Aw, Bucky, no.” ”

After the events at SHIELD Bucky goes to Clint because he knows that Clint won’t hurt him. Shenanigans ensue.

title: Knockout! 19
body:
Pairing: Fighter! Steve Rogers x Reader

Warning: Language. Hot head tempers. Cocky boys. Violence (Obvi). Nasty things said. Physical altercation (twice). Angst and lots of drama.

Last Part my peaches!!
Now We Start MC Fall!!

“Sorry Ma’am you’re going to have to leave.” The ref and Bruce look at you as they step into the room.

“Right.” You nod.

“Sorry spouses only.” Bruce gives you a sympathetic smile.

“It’s fine.” You smile at him. You turn to Steve. “I’m going to join the girls, I’ll see you out there.” You kiss him quickly, before you step out of the room, Bruce closes the door after you.

You move down the long hall, Eddie is talking to Amy, the woman who you’d had issues with over Steve. Eddie’s hand is planted on the wall, he looks up glaring at you as you get closer. A arm slips over your shoulders, pulling you into their side. You glance up, Buck is death glaring at Eddie as he escorts you towards the arena area, he nods letting you go when you reach the walk way down. You hurry towards the girls, they jump up hugging you before pulling you down into the seats.

“How are you?” Nat grins.

“Fine.” You smile.

“You look so good.” Wanda brushes a loose strand away from your face. You wore a Southside Fighter Gym T-shirt and a pair of cut off shorts, and your sneakers.

“I feel like throwing up.” You smirk.

“Steve’s got this in the bag.” Jess winks at you.

The music changes, it booms as they announce Eddie, coming down the side away from your seats. The three sitting with you, boo and lift up their hands flipping off Eddie, the crowd around you chuckles. Once again the music changes, and this time everyone around you is screaming, you turn with the girls to watch, Sam and Buck walk in front of Steve, Luke has his hands on Steve’s shoulders and Clint and Tony at his sides.

You whistle, clapping loudly, Steve smirks at you as he stops, getting his tape checked again and the cutman checks his face and healed cuts. He pulls his T-shirt over his head, before stepping towards you, you stand up to meet him. He kisses you quickly, pressing his shirt into your hand.

“Make smart moves.” You speak loud enough for him to hear you over the crowd and music. He chuckles, nodding.

“Marry me.” He grins at you, before kissing you again. Only this time your stunned, you don’t kiss him back.

He turns heading up the steps to the cage, without waiting for you to respond. Eddie and Steve move towards the center of the cage where the ref is waiting. Eddie glares at Steve, Eddie’s nose was still black and blue, his eyes still faintly bruised as well. Steve looks rather smug, he says something, nodding towards Eddie, Eddie’s face hardens. Steve was taunting him. Buck steps over to you, you were still rooted to the spot Steve left you in.

“You okay?” Buck calls. You nod, shuffling back, you sit down. He watches you a moment longer before he nods, heading back to his place at Steve’s corner.

Eddie refuses to tap fists with Steve, the ref waves them off. The ref slices the air with his hand and they storm at each other, kicks, punches, blocks and dancing around. Steve’s playing with him. Steve hits Eddie around the middle, taking Eddie to the mat, hits, blocks and Steve lets Eddie go. Steve was letting Eddie get up, but Steve was already on his feet waiting. Eddie looked a little nervous, why would he let him up. Steve does the same thing a few more times, taking Eddie down, throwing hits, before he lets Eddie get up, again. The bell rings, and they move to their corners, you shake your head, standing up you yell for Buck. He turns coming for you quickly.

“Doll?” He calls, leaning in close so you could hear each other.

“Tell him, tell him I said yes.” You call back. He looks at you funny, before he nods, turning and jogging back to the cage. He pulls himself up on the side, saying something to Steve who’s looking over at him. They both look over at you, you wink at Steve before you settle back into your seat. Steve laughs before he nods at Clint. The ref warning them to ready up, once again a slice of the air and they’re storming at each other.

It was happening fast, suddenly they’re slamming into the mat. Eddie gets his arm around the back of Steve’s neck, he’s caught him in a triangle hold, using Steve’s own arm to choke him out. Steve’s trapped you can see him wincing as he struggles, the ribs giving him problems like Bruce warned him. Eddie’s trying to final the hold, Steve’s struggling hard. Your hands are over your mouth as you watch in panic.

The thing about Eddie is he was just too cocky for his own good, he underestimated his opponent. You watched, Steve manage to get his feet under him, taking Eddie up with him as he brings himself up to full height.

“No shit.” Nat gasps.

“Holy fuck!” Jess claps.

“This is going to hurt.” Wanda winces.

Bucky, Sam, and Luke watch in pure shock, your own mouth falls open. Eddie is hunched over Steve, looking eye to eye at Steve’s full height, Eddie looks terrified. Eddie is perched on Steve’s shoulders, he can’t get away without taking a fall, he’s at Steve’s mercy. It felt like the arena had gone still, everyone waiting, watching, wondering how bad this was going to come out.

Steve snaps forward, slamming Eddie’s back into the mat with a nasty sound. Steve breaks free, dropping to his knees, one hit, two hit, and a third for good measure and the ref is pulling him back. Eddie’s out cold. The crowd is deafening instantly. The ref holds up Steve’s hand, the announcer drawing out Steve’s name. The post interview starts as Eddie is limping off out of the cage with help.

“That was the craziest fight I have to say I’ve ever watched Rogers!” The interviewer grins.

“Thanks.” Steve chuckles. “I wanted this fight to be an all-out, never forget.” Steve nods as Luke hands him a towel, letting him wipe his face off.

“You got it alright, I don’t think anyone, but maybe Brock might forget this fight. That was one amazing slam.” He grins. “So, any words for your next challenger? How long till we see your next fight?” He asks. Steve glances over back at you. He looks back at the interviewer.

“Nope. This was my final fight. I officially retire when I leave this cage.” Steve chuckles.

“Any reason why?” The interviewer looks shocked, you were sure you looked the same.

“I’m going to get married, have a family, take up coaching. I’m ready for an easy life.” Steve laughs. Luke Buck, Sam, Tony and Clint are cheering. Nat, Wanda and Jess are staring at you, you laugh your hands covering your face. He pats the interviewer on the shoulder, he and the guys leave the cage. Steve jogs over to where you were still sitting.

“You won.” You laugh, it sounded funny, like it was far too emotional, you were scared when Eddie had the upper hand. Steve grins, pulling you up and into him.

“Told you I knew what I was going to do after this fight.” He grinned, leaning down to kiss you.

“You just couldn’t share the ideas with me.” You laugh, rolling your eyes.

“What fun is that?” He smirks.

The rest of the group is joining the two of you. People asking questions, congratulating Steve, the two of you. Steve’s arm stays around your waist as he walks you towards the rooms, your friends, your little misfit family following. Funny how a few short months ago, everything was completely different when you first laid eyes on Steve. You had everything you wanted in life, everything you’d been hoping for one day.

trail.content_raw:
Pairing: Fighter! Steve Rogers x Reader

Warning: Language. Hot head tempers. Cocky boys. Violence (Obvi). Nasty things said. Physical altercation (twice). Angst and lots of drama.

Last Part my peaches!!
Now We Start MC Fall!!

[[MORE]]

“Sorry Ma’am you’re going to have to leave.” The ref and Bruce look at you as they step into the room.

“Right.” You nod.

“Sorry spouses only.” Bruce gives you a sympathetic smile.

“It’s fine.” You smile at him. You turn to Steve. “I’m going to join the girls, I’ll see you out there.” You kiss him quickly, before you step out of the room, Bruce closes the door after you.

You move down the long hall, Eddie is talking to Amy, the woman who you’d had issues with over Steve. Eddie’s hand is planted on the wall, he looks up glaring at you as you get closer. A arm slips over your shoulders, pulling you into their side. You glance up, Buck is death glaring at Eddie as he escorts you towards the arena area, he nods letting you go when you reach the walk way down. You hurry towards the girls, they jump up hugging you before pulling you down into the seats.

“How are you?” Nat grins.

“Fine.” You smile.

“You look so good.” Wanda brushes a loose strand away from your face. You wore a Southside Fighter Gym T-shirt and a pair of cut off shorts, and your sneakers.

“I feel like throwing up.” You smirk.

“Steve’s got this in the bag.” Jess winks at you.

The music changes, it booms as they announce Eddie, coming down the side away from your seats. The three sitting with you, boo and lift up their hands flipping off Eddie, the crowd around you chuckles. Once again the music changes, and this time everyone around you is screaming, you turn with the girls to watch, Sam and Buck walk in front of Steve, Luke has his hands on Steve’s shoulders and Clint and Tony at his sides.

You whistle, clapping loudly, Steve smirks at you as he stops, getting his tape checked again and the cutman checks his face and healed cuts. He pulls his T-shirt over his head, before stepping towards you, you stand up to meet him. He kisses you quickly, pressing his shirt into your hand.

“Make smart moves.” You speak loud enough for him to hear you over the crowd and music. He chuckles, nodding.

“Marry me.” He grins at you, before kissing you again. Only this time your stunned, you don’t kiss him back.

He turns heading up the steps to the cage, without waiting for you to respond. Eddie and Steve move towards the center of the cage where the ref is waiting. Eddie glares at Steve, Eddie’s nose was still black and blue, his eyes still faintly bruised as well. Steve looks rather smug, he says something, nodding towards Eddie, Eddie’s face hardens. Steve was taunting him. Buck steps over to you, you were still rooted to the spot Steve left you in.

“You okay?” Buck calls. You nod, shuffling back, you sit down. He watches you a moment longer before he nods, heading back to his place at Steve’s corner.

Eddie refuses to tap fists with Steve, the ref waves them off. The ref slices the air with his hand and they storm at each other, kicks, punches, blocks and dancing around. Steve’s playing with him. Steve hits Eddie around the middle, taking Eddie to the mat, hits, blocks and Steve lets Eddie go. Steve was letting Eddie get up, but Steve was already on his feet waiting. Eddie looked a little nervous, why would he let him up. Steve does the same thing a few more times, taking Eddie down, throwing hits, before he lets Eddie get up, again. The bell rings, and they move to their corners, you shake your head, standing up you yell for Buck. He turns coming for you quickly.

“Doll?” He calls, leaning in close so you could hear each other.

“Tell him, tell him I said yes.” You call back. He looks at you funny, before he nods, turning and jogging back to the cage. He pulls himself up on the side, saying something to Steve who’s looking over at him. They both look over at you, you wink at Steve before you settle back into your seat. Steve laughs before he nods at Clint. The ref warning them to ready up, once again a slice of the air and they’re storming at each other.

It was happening fast, suddenly they’re slamming into the mat. Eddie gets his arm around the back of Steve’s neck, he’s caught him in a triangle hold, using Steve’s own arm to choke him out. Steve’s trapped you can see him wincing as he struggles, the ribs giving him problems like Bruce warned him. Eddie’s trying to final the hold, Steve’s struggling hard. Your hands are over your mouth as you watch in panic.

The thing about Eddie is he was just too cocky for his own good, he underestimated his opponent. You watched, Steve manage to get his feet under him, taking Eddie up with him as he brings himself up to full height.

“No shit.” Nat gasps.

“Holy fuck!” Jess claps.

“This is going to hurt.” Wanda winces.

Bucky, Sam, and Luke watch in pure shock, your own mouth falls open. Eddie is hunched over Steve, looking eye to eye at Steve’s full height, Eddie looks terrified. Eddie is perched on Steve’s shoulders, he can’t get away without taking a fall, he’s at Steve’s mercy. It felt like the arena had gone still, everyone waiting, watching, wondering how bad this was going to come out.

Steve snaps forward, slamming Eddie’s back into the mat with a nasty sound. Steve breaks free, dropping to his knees, one hit, two hit, and a third for good measure and the ref is pulling him back. Eddie’s out cold. The crowd is deafening instantly. The ref holds up Steve’s hand, the announcer drawing out Steve’s name. The post interview starts as Eddie is limping off out of the cage with help.

“That was the craziest fight I have to say I’ve ever watched Rogers!” The interviewer grins.

“Thanks.” Steve chuckles. “I wanted this fight to be an all-out, never forget.” Steve nods as Luke hands him a towel, letting him wipe his face off.

“You got it alright, I don’t think anyone, but maybe Brock might forget this fight. That was one amazing slam.” He grins. “So, any words for your next challenger? How long till we see your next fight?” He asks. Steve glances over back at you. He looks back at the interviewer.

“Nope. This was my final fight. I officially retire when I leave this cage.” Steve chuckles.

“Any reason why?” The interviewer looks shocked, you were sure you looked the same.

“I’m going to get married, have a family, take up coaching. I’m ready for an easy life.” Steve laughs. Luke Buck, Sam, Tony and Clint are cheering. Nat, Wanda and Jess are staring at you, you laugh your hands covering your face. He pats the interviewer on the shoulder, he and the guys leave the cage. Steve jogs over to where you were still sitting.

“You won.” You laugh, it sounded funny, like it was far too emotional, you were scared when Eddie had the upper hand. Steve grins, pulling you up and into him.

“Told you I knew what I was going to do after this fight.” He grinned, leaning down to kiss you.

“You just couldn’t share the ideas with me.” You laugh, rolling your eyes.

“What fun is that?” He smirks.

The rest of the group is joining the two of you. People asking questions, congratulating Steve, the two of you. Steve’s arm stays around your waist as he walks you towards the rooms, your friends, your little misfit family following. Funny how a few short months ago, everything was completely different when you first laid eyes on Steve. You had everything you wanted in life, everything you’d been hoping for one day.
